block content 
    h1.bd-title#content Tables
    p.bd-lead Documentation and examples for opt-in styling of tables (given their prevalent use in JavaScript plugins) with Bootstrap.
    
    h2#examples Examples
    p
        | Due to the widespread use of tables across third-party widgets like calendars and date pickers, we’ve designed our tables to be 
        strong opt-in
        | . Just add the base class 
        code.highlighter-rouge .table
        |  to any 
        code.highlighter-rouge &lt;table&gt;
        | , then extend with custom styles or our various included modifier classes.
    p
        | Using the most basic table markup, here’s how 
        code.highlighter-rouge .table
        | -based tables look in Bootstrap. 
        strong All table styles are inherited in Bootstrap 4
        | , meaning any nested tables will be styled in the same manner as the parent.
    .bd-example
        -
            var head =  ['#','First','Last','Handle']
            var data = [
                        ['1','Mark','Otto','@mdo'],
                        ['2','Jacob','Thornton','@fat'],
                        ['3','Larry','the Bird','@twitter']
                       ]
        +table(head,data,'','','','head')
    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.js.
                //- Table mixins
                //- @mixin +table(header, data, type,typehead, typerow, typecol, itemrow, itemcol, responsive)
                //- @param {array} header: data header - ['head 1', 'head 2', '...']
                //- @param {array} data: data content - [['col 1', 'col 2', '...'], ['col 1', 'col 2', '...'],['...', '...', '...']]
                //- @param {string} type: type of table
                //- @param {string} typehead: type of header 
                //- @param {string} typerow: type of row 
                //- @param {string} typecol: type of col
                //- @param {number} itemrow: number type of row (0, 1, 2, 3, ... 'all')
                //- @param {number} itemcol: number type of col
                //- @param {boolean} responsive: responsive table: '', 'sm', 'md', 'lg', 'xl'

                -
                    var head =  ['#','First','Last','Handle']
                    var data = [
                                ['1','Mark','Otto','@mdo'],
                                ['2','Jacob','Thornton','@fat'],
                                ['3','Larry','the Bird','@twitter']
                            ]
                +table(head,data,'','','','head')
    p
        | You can also invert the colors—with light text on dark backgrounds—with 
        code.highlighter-rouge .table-dark
        | .
    .bd-example
        +table-dark(head,data)
        
    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.js.
