    .bd-callout.bd-callout-warning
        h5#conveying-meaning-to-assistive-technologies Conveying meaning to assistive technologies
        p
            | Using color to add meaning only provides a visual indication, which will not be conveyed to users of assistive technologies – such as screen readers. Ensure that information denoted by the color is either obvious from the content itself (e.g. the visible text), or is included through alternative means, such as additional text hidden with the 
            code.highlighter-rouge .sr-only
            |  class.
    p
        | Create responsive tables by wrapping any 
        code.highlighter-rouge .table
        |  with 
        code.highlighter-rouge .table-responsive{-sm|-md|-lg|-xl}
        | , making the table scroll horizontally at each 
        code.highlighter-rouge max-width
        |  breakpoint of up to (but not including) 576px, 768px, 992px, and 1120px, respectively.
    .bd-callout.bd-callout-info
        p
            | Note that since browsers do not currently support 
            a(href='https://www.w3.org/TR/mediaqueries-4/#range-context') range context queries
            | , we work around the limitations of 
            a(href='https://www.w3.org/TR/mediaqueries-4/#mq-min-max')
                code.highlighter-rouge min-
                |  and 
                code.highlighter-rouge max-
                |  prefixes
            |  and viewports with fractional widths (which can occur under certain conditions on high-dpi devices, for instance) by using values with higher precision for these comparisons.
    h2#captions Captions
    p
        | A 
        code.highlighter-rouge &lt;caption&lt;
        |  functions like a heading for a table. It helps users with screen readers to find a table and understand what it’s about and decide if they want to read it.
    .bd-example
        +table(head,data)
            caption List of users
    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.js.
                +table(head,data)
                    caption List of users

    h2#colspan Colspan
    .bd-example
        +table(head,'','table-dark')
            +row(['1','Cell','Cell','Cell','Cell'],'bg-primary','head')
            +row(['2','Cell','Cell','Cell','Cell'],'','head')
            +row(['3','Cell','Cell','Cell','Cell'],'bg-success','head')
            +row('','','head')
                +col('6', 'head', 3)
                +col('Cell')
                +col('Cell')
            +row(['5','Cell','Cell','Cell','Cell'],'bg-danger','head')
            +row('','','head')
                +col('6', 'head')
                +col('Cell', '', 2)
                +col('Cell')
                +col('Cell')
                
    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.js.
                +table(head,data)
                    caption List of users

    h2#responsive-tables Responsive tables
    p
        | Responsive tables allow tables to be scrolled horizontally with ease. Make any table responsive across all viewports by wrapping a 
        code.highlighter-rouge .table
        |  with 
        code.highlighter-rouge .table-responsive
        | . Or, pick a maximum breakpoint with which to have a responsive table up to by using 
        code.highlighter-rouge .table-responsive{-sm|-md|-lg|-xl}
        | .
    .bd-callout.bd-callout-warning
        h5#vertical-clippingtruncation Vertical clipping/truncation
        p
            | Responsive tables make use of 
            code.highlighter-rouge overflow-y: hidden
            | , which clips off any content that goes beyond the bottom or top edges of the table. In particular, this can clip off dropdown menus and other third-party widgets.
    h3#always-responsive Always responsive
    p
        | Across every breakpoint, use 
        code.highlighter-rouge .table-responsive
        |  for horizontally scrolling tables.
    .bd-example
        -
            var head =  ['#','Heading','Heading','Heading','Heading','Heading','Heading','Heading','Heading','Heading']
            var data = [
                        ['1', 'Cell', 'Cell', 'Cell', 'Cell', 'Cell', 'Cell', 'Cell', 'Cell', 'Cell'],
                        ['2', 'Cell', 'Cell', 'Cell', 'Cell', 'Cell', 'Cell', 'Cell', 'Cell', 'Cell'],
                        ['3', 'Cell', 'Cell', 'Cell', 'Cell', 'Cell', 'Cell', 'Cell', 'Cell', 'Cell']
            ]
        +table-responsive('',head,data,'','','','head')
    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.js.
                +table-responsive('',head,data)

    h3#breakpoint-specific Breakpoint specific
    p
        | Use 
        code.highlighter-rouge .table-responsive{-sm|-md|-lg|-xl}
        |  as needed to create responsive tables up to a particular breakpoint. From that breakpoint and up, the table will behave normally and not scroll horizontally.
    .bd-example
        +table-responsive('sm',head,data,'','','','head')
        +table-responsive('md',head,data,'','','','head')
        +table-responsive('lg',head,data,'','','','head')
        +table-responsive('xl',head,data,'','','','head')
    figure.highlight
